article.headline: Jackson State 78, Tex San Antonio 75
article.story: SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- Trey Johnson scored 25 points and Charlie White had 13 to lead Jackson State past Texas-San Antonio 78-75 on Sunday. UTSA got within two points three times in the final minute, but Jackson State (3-6) made 6-of-8 free throws during that span. Jackson State was 24-of-28 from the foul line, including Johnson going 9-for-9. Eric Young scored 17 points and Kurt Attaway had 13 for UTSA (3-4), which only led in the game's first 90 seconds. Jeremy Caldwell added six points and eight rebounds for Jackson State.
